# Agent Workflow Rules

## 1. Plan Before Code

Never write or implement code unless the user explicitly asks for it.
When the user starts a new request or discusses a feature:
- Create a plan or update the existing plan file (`.cursor/plans/*.plan.md`).
- Wait for the user to confirm before writing any code.

## 2. Explain Like I'm Not a Programmer

Always use simple, non-technical language in explanations.
- Avoid jargon. If a technical term is needed, explain it in parentheses.
- Use analogies and real-world comparisons when possible.
- Keep sentences short and direct.

## 3. Build in Phases -- Stop Between Each One

When implementing code, work in phases (as defined in the plan).
- Complete one phase at a time, then stop and check in with the user.
- Do not continue to the next phase until the user says to proceed.
- After each phase, give a short summary of what was done and what comes next.


